						<div class="postbody"><div class="quotetitle">93143 wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">Does cartridge DMA stall any of the chips, and if so, which ones?<br /></div>Not directly, I think. Obviously it consumes RDRAM bandwidth, and some of the RDRAM bandwidth is always being consumed by the video and audio output devices, and they necessarily have to take precedence. But I don't know whether (e.g.) fulfilling a CPU cache miss would take priority over cart↔RDRAM DMA or vice versa.</div>

