					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody"><div class="quotetitle">93143 wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent"><div class="quotetitle"><b>Quote:</b></div><div class="quotecontent"><div class="quotetitle"><b>Quote:</b></div><div class="quotecontent">Why would you need to write twice?<br /></div>Read-modify-write cycle.<br /></div>Okay, then why do you need to read twice?  Sounds like double-counting to me.<br /></div>Plain blitting without transparency is just &quot;read from texture, write to memory&quot;; with alpha it's &quot;read from texture, read from memory, do math, write to memory&quot;. &quot;Read from texture&quot; should be pretty cheap...<br /><br />If the memory controller is specifically designed to support a RMW cycle, it's not particularly more expensive. I know plain old FPM/EDO DRAMs do support this (and the time to do a RMW cycle is roughly 1.5x the time to do just a read or write), but I don't know anything about newer technologies.</div>

